raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: igwn-ligolw
  version: 2.1.1

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/igwn_ligolw-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4ca1860e79ec5e25d575ae4e27fa8035a269af6fcda9da33f090ceb85b34b64b

build:
  number: 0
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation
  skip:
    - win
    - "python_impl != 'cpython'"

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    # extras for cross-compiling:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - python
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools >=64
    - setuptools-scm >=8
  run:
    - igwn-segments
    - numpy
    - python
    - python-dateutil
    - pyyaml
    - tqdm

tests:
  - files:
      source:
        - test
    requirements:
      run:
        - libxml2
        - make
        - matplotlib-base
        - pip
        - pytest-benchmark
        - pytest-doctestplus
        - python-lal
        - xz-tools
    script:
      - python -m pip check
      - python -m pip show igwn-ligolw
      - python -m pytest test
      - pytest --doctest-plus --pyargs igwn_ligolw
      - make -C test
      - igwn_ligolw_add --help
      - igwn_ligolw_cut --help
      - igwn_ligolw_no_ilwdchar --help
      - igwn_ligolw_print --help
      - igwn_ligolw_run_sqlite --help
      - igwn_ligolw_segments --help
      - igwn_ligolw_sqlite --help

about:
  summary: Python LIGO Light-Weight XML I/O Library
  description: |
    The LIGO Light-Weight XML format is used extensively by compact object
    detection pipeline and associated tool sets.
    This package provides a Python I/O library for reading, writing, and
    interacting with documents in this format.
  homepage: https://git.ligo.org/computing/software/igwn-ligolw/
  repository: https://git.ligo.org/computing/software/igwn-ligolw.git
  documentation: https://igwn-ligolw.readthedocs.io
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - duncanmmacleod
    - lpsinger
    - titodalcanton
